race.comment: Very tough for the picnic horses in the Corinthian. ANNOY'EN ONE (7) tackled a BM56 at Tatura fresh and wasn't beaten far despite finishing eighth. His form at the picnics last preparation was rock solid and he can run well. STREET SWAGGER (5) is a chance off the run in a Class 2 at Dubbo two starts ago. ELLY DEE (2) resumes having last been seen running fourth in a BM58 at Moe which is strong form for this. HAWKESTONE (6) returns from a lay-off. Placed in a recent jump-out. Opened last campaign with a fifth at Woolamai over 1008m. Has the right credentials. STIRRUP (4) seasoned galloper who should appreciate the step up in journey after two runs from a spell, the latest when seventh over 1005m. Include.
